Account Takeover via OAuth Token Injection in setToken endpoint - Bingo Blitz
Summary:
The endpoint /bingo-app/public/non-authenticated/oc/setToken accepts any valid
OneConnect JWT without verifying that it belongs to the current session or requester.
An attacker who obtains another user's access_token can inject it into this endpoint
and gain full authenticated access to the victim's account without knowing their password.
Steps To Reproduce:
Victim authenticates via OneConnect on play.bingoblitzvip.com, generating a JWT via:
POST https://one-zuul.bingoblitz.com/one/oauth/token
Attacker obtains victim's access_token (via XSS, network interception, or other means)
Attacker calls setToken with victim's token from a clean session (no prior auth):
POST /bingo-app/public/non-authenticated/oc/setToken HTTP/2
Host: play.bingoblitzvip.com
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded
access_token=<victim_jwt>
Server responds success:true and sets octoken=<victim_jwt> as HttpOnly cookie
Attacker accesses https://play.bingoblitzvip.com/oc using those cookies and is
authenticated as the victim. Server confirms with victim's data in response:
email_field=joacoroller-test1@wearehackerone.com
buffalo_id=1047552765
Note: Same vulnerability confirmed on play.bingoblitz.com
Recommendations:
Validate that the access_token belongs to the currently authenticated session before setting it as a cookie
Bind the token to the session ID or device fingerprint server-side
Implement rate limiting on the setToken endpoint
Verify the token against one-zuul before accepting it
Supporting Material/References:
Screenshot 1: Burp Suite - POST /one/oauth/token response showing test1 access_token (credential_value: joacoroller-test1@wearehackerone.com)
Screenshot 2: Burp Suite Repeater - POST /bingo-app/public/non-authenticated/oc/setToken with no session cookies, response shows success:true and octoken cookie being set
Screenshot 3: Terminal - Full PoC showing token injection resulting in authenticated session as joacoroller-test1@wearehackerone.com (buffalo_id: 1047552765)
Both test accounts (joacoroller-test1 and joacoroller-test2) are registered
under @wearehackerone.com as per program rules.
Impact
An attacker who obtains a valid OneConnect access_token belonging to another user
can immediately take over that account by injecting the token into the setToken
endpoint. No password or device access is required.
Successful exploitation allows the attacker to:
Access the victim's Bingo Blitz account and all associated data (PII, game progress)
Spend the victim's in-game currency and purchased items
Access the victim's email address and buffalo_id
Potentially pivot to other Playtika games sharing the same OneConnect SSO
